  "text": "The results of these studies of both rodents and humans provide evidence that endocannabinoid signaling is changed -at least in some brain regions and, perhaps, in the periphery -during depression. The alterations observed in the hippocampus, prefrontal cortex and thalamus are of particular interest, given the likely involvement of these neural structures in the regulation of emotion [CITATION_1] .",
